<emphasis box="[889,1020,1353,1377]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="526">B. thaiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having posteroventral appendages on the pygoghore, but can be distinguished by the bifurcated apical appendages.
</paragraph>
